Description: A small fragment of pottery: red on the surface but black in the centre of the section, with an incised inscription of two hieroglyphs on the exterior surface. Surface rather worn.
Curator's comments: Compare W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pl. LVII, 1289, 1317. Bibliography: E. Naville, ‘The cemeteries of Abydos’ I (London, 1913), I, 37 and pl.XV.
